6/29/83 forum request: next_seen, ns

Syntax:  ns {trans_spec} {-control_args}


Syntax as an active request:  [ns {trans_spec} {-control_args}]


Function:
Prints or returns the transaction index of the first transaction after the
specified transaction which has been marked as seen, or after the current
transaction if no trans_spec is given.


Arguments:
trans_spec
   is the transaction for which the next_seen transaction is desired.


Control arguments:
-include_deleted, -idl
   print or return the index of the next_seen transaction even if it
   is deleted.
-only_deleted, -odl
   print or return the index of the next_seen deleted transaction.
-only_non_deleted, -ondl
   print or return the index of the next_seen non-deleted transaction.
   (Default)
